{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:02:46.134Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Train/Val/Test Splits"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the fundamental practice of dividing a dataset into three independent subsets to ensure models are trained properly, tuned without bias, and evaluated on completely unseen data — preventing overfitting and ensuring the model generalizes to real-world scenarios."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The dataset is split into three parts with distinct purposes:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Set"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Purpose"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Does"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training Set"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Teach the model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fits model parameters (weights, biases, coefficients)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Validation Set"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tune hyperparameters"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Evaluates performance during tuning, prevents overfitting to training data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Test Set"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Final evaluation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assesses generalization on unseen data, never used during training/tuning"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key principle"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Three independent sets ensure the model learns patterns, we tune without cheating, and we get an unbiased final performance estimate."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why It Matters"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Solution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Validation prevents tuning to training data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data snooping"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test set stays hidden until final evaluation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Poor generalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test set approximates real-world performance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Unreliable evaluation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Correct splitting ensures trustworthy model assessment"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "If you trained and tested on the same data"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Model appears perfect on training but fails on new data — overfitting."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each Set's Role"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Train/Val/Test Splits — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training Set"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Purpose"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Teach the model to learn patterns"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What happens"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Model "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fits parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (weights in neural nets, slope/intercept in linear regression)\n- Learns underlying patterns and relationships\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Largest portion"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of data (60–80%)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Training: Model learns from this data\nmodel.fit(X_train, y_train)"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Determines what the model knows before evaluation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Validation Set"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Purpose"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Tune hyperparameters and prevent overfitting"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What happens"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Tune hyperparameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (learning rate, tree depth, regularization)\n- Monitor "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "validation loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to decide when to stop training\n- Compare different algorithms and parameter choices\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Intermediate portion"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (15–30%)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Validation: Tune model settings\ny_pred_val = model.predict(X_val)\nprint(accuracy_score(y_val, y_pred_val))  # Check performance"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Acts as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "independent, unbiased dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for comparing algorithms"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Helps decide which model/parameters to use in production"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Test Set"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Purpose"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Final unbiased evaluation of generalization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What happens"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Final holdout dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — never used during training or tuning\n- Represents "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "real-world unseen data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " performance\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Smallest portion"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (10–20%)\n- Check "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "only once"}, {"type": "text", "text": " at the very end"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Test: Final evaluation (only once!)\ny_pred_test = model.predict(X_test)\nprint(accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_test))  # Final performance"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Critical rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Never peek at test performance before selecting model"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Peeking = overfitting → unreliable production expectations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical Split Ratios"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dataset Size"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Ratio"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Notes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "80% train, 20% test"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use cross-validation for validation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Medium datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "70% train, 15% val, 15% test"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common for large datasets"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "60% train, 20% val, 20% test"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "More validation/test for small data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Very large (ImageNet)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "95%+ train, 5% test"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Even 1–5% test is enough"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Exact ratio depends on dataset size."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to Split: Two-Step Process"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "train/val/test"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", split dataset twice:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Step 1: First split (80% model + 20% test)\nX_model, X_test, y_model, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=0)\n\n# Step 2: Second split (75% train + 25% val of remaining 80%)\nX_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(X_model, y_model, test_size=0.25, random_state=0)\n\n# Result: 60% train, 20% val, 20% test overall"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "If already given separate train/val/test"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Skip first split, use directly."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visual Diagram"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Original Dataset\n    │\n    ├─→ Training Set (60-80%)  → Model learns patterns\n    │\n    ├─→ Validation Set (15-30%) → Tune hyperparameters\n    │\n    └─→ Test Set (10-20%)      → Final evaluation (only once!)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Cross-Validation Instead"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scenario"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "k-fold cross-validation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Limited data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-validation for better estimate"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Train/Val/Test split"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "k-fold cross-validation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Split data into "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "k"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " folds (e.g., 5)\n- Train on "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "k-1"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " folds, validate on remaining fold\n- Repeat for all folds, average performance\n- More reliable estimate, especially when data is limited"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If you're sure of model/hyperparameters and dataset is very small → train/test split only."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best Practices"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Practice"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reason"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stratify"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in imbalanced classification"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Maintain class distribution across splits"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevent data leakage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fit preprocessing only on training data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Treat test set as black box"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use only once at the end"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fixed random seed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reproducible splits"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Compare train vs. test accuracy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Detect overfitting/underfitting"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Holding out data reduces training size → validate carefully and refit on train+validation before final test."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example Workflow"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# 1. Split data\nX_train, X_val, X_test, y_train, y_val, y_test = create_splits(X, y)\n\n# 2. Train model\nmodel.fit(X_train, y_train)\n\n# 3. Evaluate on validation (tune hyperparameters)\ny_pred_val = model.predict(X_val)\nval_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_val, y_pred_val)\n\n# 4. After tuning, test on final test set (one-time only!)\ny_pred_test = model.predict(X_test)\ntest_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_test)\n\n# 5. Compare\nprint(f\"Train accuracy: {train_accuracy:.2%}\")\nprint(f\"Test accuracy: {test_accuracy:.2%}\")\n# If train >> test → overfitting"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Train set"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (60-80%) = teaches model, fits parameters"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Validation set"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (15-30%) = tunes hyperparameters, prevents overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Test set"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (10-20%) = final evaluation on unseen data, never peek"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Three independent sets"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = ensures trustworthy evaluation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Don't peek at test"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = prevents overfitting to evaluation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Split twice"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = 80%→train/val, 20%→test"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small datasets"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = use k-fold cross-validation instead"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large datasets"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = train/val/test split works"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stratify"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = maintain class balance in imbalanced data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevent leakage"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = fit preprocessing only on training data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Compare accuracies"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = train vs. test reveals overfitting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Train/Val/Test splits are the \"honest evaluation system\" — training teaches the model, validation tunes it without cheating, and test provides the final unbiased performance on completely unseen data, ensuring models generalize to real-world scenarios and preventing overfitting."}]}]}}